Reference-contexts: 1 Introduction We have defined temporal extensions to HTML <ref> [1] </ref> to allow specification and playback of synchronized multimedia presentations in the WWW context. Components of such presentations may include continuous multimedia data (audio and video clips) either stored on WWW servers or coming from live-data sources.
